& [ManifestCheckpointProbeValidationDesign] is the design contract for validating checkpoint Shaliach probe evidence
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-30T12:40:00Z
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [related_design] coordination/manifest_shaliach_probe_validation_design.sop
  @ [related_design] coordination/cross_artifact_checkpoint_probe_design.sop
  @ [checkpoint_artifact] coordination/long_run_checkpoint.sop
  @ [manifest_module] src/negotiated_agent/run_manifest.py

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is checkpoint_probe_presence_validation_not_semantic_review
  + [primary_goal] is let validation tools confirm that a long-run checkpoint recorded Shaliach cross-artifact probe evidence
  + [non_goal] is re-running the checkpoint harness
  + [non_goal] is deciding whether Shaliach findings are true
  + [non_goal] is approving a Manager gate, advancing a frontier, or applying generated files

& [CheckpointEvidenceFields] is the minimum evidence vocabulary
  + [field] is checkpoint_status
  + [field] is shaliach_cross_artifact_status
  + [field] is HarnessCommand shaliach_cross_artifact_probe returncode
  + [field] is HarnessCommand shaliach_cross_artifact_probe stdout_tail
  + [field] is HarnessCommand shaliach_cross_artifact_probe authority_boundary
  + [authority_boundary] is field_presence_and_status_not_probe_reexecution

& [ValidationRules] is the deterministic rule set
  + [rule] is checkpoint proof is acceptable when shaliach_cross_artifact_status is passed and the probe command returncode is 0
  + [rule] is checkpoint proof is incomplete when shaliach_cross_artifact_status is not_run or the probe command is absent
  + [rule] is checkpoint proof is failed when shaliach_cross_artifact_status is failed or the probe command returncode is nonzero other than the explicit not_run code
  + [rule] is validator must preserve openai_health_status as a separate non-gating environment field
  + [rule] is validator must report checkpoint proof status without mutating the checkpoint or run artifacts
  + [authority_boundary] is proof_status_validation_not_human_or_manager_approval

& [ImplementationShape] is the intended safe split
  + [slice_1] is add a parser for the checkpoint Shaliach probe fields
  + [slice_2] is add a pure validator that returns passed incomplete or failed evidence status
  + [slice_3] is expose an optional CLI or integrate the validator beside run manifest validation
  + [slice_4] is document the operator sequence for manifest validation followed by checkpoint proof validation
  + [authority_boundary] is validation_helper_not_long_run_execution

& [ProofExpectations] is the minimum implementation proof
  + [test_case] is checkpoint proof validates passed status with returncode 0
  + [test_case] is checkpoint proof reports incomplete when probe status is not_run
  + [test_case] is checkpoint proof rejects failed probe status
  + [test_case] is checkpoint proof rejects missing probe command fields
  + [test_case] is openai_health_status remains non-gating and separately reported
  + [test_case] is validation never mutates checkpoint or run artifacts
